FBIS3-8700 "dreeu050_h_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Mar 1994 HUNGARY Army Chief of Staff Promoted LD1203163694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 1200 GMT 12 Mar 94 LD1203163694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Language: Hungarian Article Type:BFN [Text] Hungarian President Arpad Goncz has promoted Lieutenant-General Janos Deak, Hungarian Army commander and chief of staff, to the rank of colonel-general. On the occasion of the 15 March holiday, Arpad Goncz promoted 11 colonels, four of them to major general and seven of them to brigadier general. This was the first occasion that somebody was promoted to the rank of brigadier general, a rank established in the Defense Law passed in January. Defense Minister Lajos Fur and Interior Minister Imre Konya were also present at the ceremony.
